def: In the manner of courts; politely; gracefully; elegantly.They can produce nothing so courtly writ. Dryden
The pistils of a flower, taken collectively. See Illust. ofCarpophore.
The doctrine of refracted sound; diacoustics.
A combining form fr. Gr. "o`los whole.
To feel or express undue care and anxiety; to manifestdisquietude or pain; to be fretful; to chafe; as, the child worries;the horse worries.
An insect which has the anterior pair of wings coriaceous, anddoes not use them in flight, as the earwig.
A figure bounded by three lines, and containing three angles.
Made of, secured by, or covered with, wickers or wickerwork.Ships of light timber, wickered with osier between, and covered overwith leather. Milton.
